President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint Caroline Grace Vanvick as Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the Department of Housing and Urban Development. Vanvick currently serves as Acting Assistant Secretary and Deputy Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the department. She has previously worked as a communications director and senior spokeswoman for representatives in the United States Senate and House of Representatives. Vanvick holds a B.A. from the College of Charleston and resides in Washington, D.C.

Additionally, President Trump intends to appoint Robert Dole as a Member of the Dwight D. Eisenhower Memorial Commission.